/images/sidebutton.jpg width=100 height=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Recruitment Guidelines... READ OR DIE!</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>      READ AND PLEASE FOLLOW THE GUIDELINE! </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><br>Hello from USV.  If you are interesting in applying for membership to our guild, please make sure you are at least <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  lvl 35</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> and have someone that you know in guild to speak on your behalf**.  Post in this forum and give us some information about you as well as answer these questions:<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>      What are your characters names? </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>      What level are your characters? </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>      How can we contact you?  (email)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>      What is your current guild status? </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>      (Are you still in your last guild?  Have you applied to any other guilds?)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>      Did someone refer you to this guild and/or do you have friends in USV?* </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>      Why do you wish to be a part of the USV family? </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><br>After you post your thread, I will start a poll in the member's only section that basically says &quot;Should applicant_04 be invited into USV?  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   YES</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> or <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   NO</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->&quot;.  It will stay there for <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   5 days</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, at which time you will be notified of wether you will be invited or not.<br><br>If someone objects your application, one of two things can happen. We will put your application status on hold and try to get to know you better by grouping with you.  Or someone may use their <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>      Mortal Enemy Clause</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> and you will be denied membership.  <br><br>A Mortal Enemy Clause works like this: If noob_01 wishes to join the guild and member_01 hates this person with such a passion that they would say, &quot;It's me or them... if they get invited, I leave.&quot;  Member_01 will whip out his handy dandy Mortal Enemy Clause and slap it down on the table.  Noob_01 will be denied membership to the guild forever unless member_01 leaves the guild.  Guild members get to use this clause once per calendar year, and no, clauses do not build up over the years.<br><br>If all goes good with your application, you will be notified and invited into the guild and given status to the Members Only forums.  Your application will be deleted from the Members Only forum.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  * - RL Friends and Family of a Member</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> will not have to go through the voting, but a thread will be put up with their application for 5 days in the Members Only Forum for comments.  After the 5 days, the RL Friend/Family member will be invited.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> ** - You must have a sponsor to speak for you upon applying. </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->That means that you need to put your sponsors name in your application and for your application to be approved, the said sponsor must post on the application thread in the Members Forum.<br><br><br>If you have any questions, please contact me at naharet@hotmail.com.<br><br>Good luck and hope to see you in USV soon!<br> <p><center><img src="http://www.active-is.com/~samie/images/sigbanner.jpg"><br><font color=red> Asherea Lonewolf - 55 Preserver </font><br><font color=blue> Naharet Darkhealer - 49 Cleric</font> <br> <font color=purple> <b>O